Introduction

Felix Yongbok Lee is a South Korean-Australian rapper, songwriter, dancer, and composer under JYP Entertainment. He is the lead rapper and lead dancer of Stray Kids and part of its unofficial subunit Danceracha.

Felix was scouted through an online message after school, leading to an audition where he showcased freestyle dance. He officially joined JYP Entertainment on February 24, 2017, and was introduced as a participant in the survival show Stray Kids on October 12, 2017. Although eliminated in episode 8 due to language challenges, he was reinstated in the final episode on December 19, 2017, confirming his place in the then 9-member group.

Felix debuted with Stray Kids on March 25, 2018, with the album I Am Not and its title track "District 9."

On August 22, 2023, he was announced as a house ambassador for Louis Vuitton, later featuring in multiple magazine spreads and attending global fashion week events. On March 5, 2024, he made his runway debut at Paris Fashion Week for Louis Vuitton Women's Fall-Winter 2024 Collection at Cour Carrée.

Since 2020, Felix has been a consistent donor to Save the Children, earning membership in the charity’s Honors Club. His philanthropic efforts continued with donations for disaster relief, including the Turkey–Syria earthquakes in 2023. In January 2024, he contributed ₩100 million (US$76,589.47) to the Korean Committee for UNICEF for Laotian children's sanitation and nutrition, becoming the youngest UNICEF Honors Club member. To celebrate his 24th birthday, he donated an additional ₩50 million to UNICEF for child nutrition and water sanitation in Laos and ₩50 million to World Vision for breakfast support for underprivileged children in Korea.

On September 23, 2024, Felix was officially appointed as a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador for Korea.
